{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/follow-your-passion-in-data-science-42ab66923c83", "time": 1683001331.778399, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/follow-your-passion-in-data-science-42ab66923c83/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Follow your passion in Data Science | by Przemek Chojecki | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Follow your passion in Data Science", "description": "We\u2019ve all heard \u2018follow your passion\u2019 a lot in different contexts. But in this text, I want to clarify how you can follow your passion in Data Science. The key is here: there\u2019s no the data science\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["We\u2019ve all heard \u2018follow your passion\u2019 a lot in different contexts. But in this text, I want to clarify how you can follow your passion in Data Science. The key is here: there\u2019s no the data science. Whether you prefer to dig deep into deep learning, analyse financial data or scrape the web \u2014 you\u2019ll be doing data science to different extents and in different forms. If you want to be really successful in Data Science, you have to make a commitment to yourself to follow your passion no matter the challenges you face.", "When you have a passion for something, it will give you a much greater sense of confidence and motivation. Passion can sometimes get you out of a rut but it\u2019s also a very powerful tool. Passion for something makes you see your data and what your dataset is telling you. It can also help you solve problems with different perspectives, and it can even make you a better Data Scientist. Passion is also a big reason why some people can never make a living as Data Scientists and why there are so many bad ones.", "What does this mean? If you have a passion for Data Science, it makes it easier to make a living and get the knowledge you need to make a success of Data Science. As we all know, there is an increasing amount of demand for talent in this field. And that is the reason why you should try to find the best Data Science job available in your field.", "There are many domains into which you can jump, to name a few:", "Data Mining, for example, is a method of mining data, which can be used in many fields. It can be applied for the analysis of information and to make predictions in order to develop software, games and so on. It can also be used to identify potential sources of errors in data and to find out the trends among different groups of data.", "Furthermore, those domains divide into smaller niches. For example, you can focus on data analysis of images.", "Image analysis is a data analysis technique that involves identifying images using the same techniques as are used for pattern analysis.", "Then you can ask yourself whether there are particular business areas you would like to apply data science in. That\u2019s the best way to connect with your passion. Find a particular niche you\u2019d love to deal with \u2014 maybe that\u2019s retail, maybe you have a knack for finance or health. Here options are limitless.", "As a data scientist, you will need to keep learning and developing as you progress in your career. A job will inevitably give you opportunities to work with some of the best people in the world. Some of the projects you will work on will require significant expertise and you need to be ready to get help from others.", "Don\u2019t worry! Data Science communities are very welcoming.", "Also please check out my other articles about becoming a Data Scientist:", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "AI & crypto, PhD in mathematics, Forbes 30 under 30, former Oxford fellow."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F42ab66923c83&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/s